# Scoped rule (example)

This file demonstrates Cursor's file-scoped rules (`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`). Scoped rules save
tokens by loading only when a relevant file is in context, instead of on every request.

When editing files matched by `globs` above:
- Follow `AGENTS.md` and `CODING_PHILOSOPHY.md` (the 4 layers).
- Component library first, inline UI never (Layer 3).
- Semantic `id` + BEM class on interactive elements.

> Duplicate and adapt this file per domain (e.g. `api.mdc` for `src/api/**`,
> `ui.mdc` for `src/components/**`). Keep each rule short and glob-scoped.
